						<summary>

						<p>The inscription which is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka 785, Tāraṇa (= A.D. 864)</hi> belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Amōghavarsha I.</hi> Since a larger portion of the record is seriously damaged, the contents cannot be properly made out. A grant of land seems to have been made to a hero named Chikaṇṇa. Incidentally the record refers to the observance of <hi rend="italic">vratas</hi> and <hi rend="italic">sanyāsana.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
